Maria Fredericks, Appellant, v. Alexander V. Davidson, as Sheriff, &c., Respondent. Decided June 8, 1886. Appeal from a judgment on verdict, and order denying motion for new trial. Francis B. Ohedsey, for appellant. W. Bourke Cockran, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Oh. J., Truax and O’Gorman, JJ.

Opinion by O’Gorman, J. Verdict set aside ; new trial ordered ; costs to abide event.
